Submitted By:            Combined: Douglas R. Reno (build fix) + still image + tune fix + YUV444
Date:                    2026-03-20
Initial Package Version: 1.21.2
Upstream Status:         Pending
Origin:                  Upstream (PR #1680) + three additional fixes
Description:             Fixes building libheif with SVT-AV1 4.0 and later.
                         Three changes on top of the original build fix:

                         1. Still image mode (SVT-AV1 >= 4.0.0):
                            avif=true, pred_structure=2 (random_access),
                            hierarchical_levels=0, intra_period_length=-1, fps=1/1.

                         2. tune=SSIM fallback to PSNR (SVT-AV1 >= 4.0.0):
                            SVT-AV1 4.x requires CRF for tune=SSIM but libheif uses
                            CQP. Sharp passes tune=ssim by default for .heif() calls
                            which crashes the encoder. Fall back silently to PSNR.

                         3. YUV444 by default (SVT-AV1 >= 4.0.0):
                            SVT-AV1 4.x supports YUV444 (EbColorFormat max is YUV444).
                            Returning heif_chroma_444 from svt_query_input_colorspace
                            eliminates the even-dimension requirement of YUV420, so
                            odd-sized images no longer produce a 'clap' box with
                            fractional pixel offsets that Firefox rejects per AVIF spec.
                            Sharp defaults to chromaSubsampling='4:4:4' for AVIF, so
                            this matches the caller's intent. To use 4:2:0 explicitly
                            pass chromaSubsampling:'4:2:0' in sharp avif options.

--- libheif-1.21.2.orig/libheif/plugins/encoder_svt.cc	2026-03-21 19:35:48.208245213 +0000
+++ libheif-1.21.2/libheif/plugins/encoder_svt.cc	2026-03-21 19:36:07.760250711 +0000
@@ -646,16 +646,29 @@ static void svt_set_default_parameters(v
 void svt_query_input_colorspace(heif_colorspace* colorspace, heif_chroma* chroma)
 {
   *colorspace = heif_colorspace_YCbCr;
+  // SVT-AV1 >= 4.0.0 supports YUV444 (EbColorFormat max is YUV444).
+  // 4:4:4 eliminates the chroma subsampling alignment requirement (even dimensions),
+  // so odd-sized images no longer need a 'clap' box with fractional pixel offsets
+  // that Firefox rejects. Sharp defaults to chromaSubsampling='4:4:4' for AVIF,
+  // so this matches the caller's intent. Pass chromaSubsampling='4:2:0' explicitly
+  // in sharp if smaller files are preferred (at the cost of odd-dimension issues).
+#if SVT_AV1_CHECK_VERSION(4, 0, 0)
+  *chroma = heif_chroma_444;
+#else
   *chroma = heif_chroma_420;
+#endif
 }
 
 
 void svt_query_input_colorspace2(void* encoder_raw, heif_colorspace* colorspace, heif_chroma* chroma)
 {
